    <note>Duan(1) Guan(2) [21755] Liu Caishao, WJ, 12.16b-20a; Wang Tinggui, WJ, 44.7a-9a (wife, born Peng, who died in 1144 at age 58). Wang(2) Tinggui [12158] describes the Duan(1) as a famous classicist family (ming rujia), and Zhou(1) Bida [7197], in his funerary inscription for Guan(2)'s lineage nephew, Yuankai [21791], says that beginning with the generation of Guan(2)'s uncle and Yuankai's grandfather, Shichen [21789], the lineage rapidly propagated and elder and youger brothers followed each other in earning degrees--the Duan(1) were called a classicist family (rujia). CBD, 2, 1701.</note>
